sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Poller as EventPoller
    participant ETbl as Databricks<br/>Events Table
    participant Val as Validators
    participant SOp as SyncOperator
    participant DData as Databricks<br/>Source Data
    participant SQL as SQL Server
    participant WS as WebSocket<br/>Subscribers

    Note over Poller,SQL: Poll cycle (periodic or manual trigger)

    Poller->>ETbl: SELECT * WHERE status = 'pending'
    ETbl-->>Poller: SyncEvent[] (batch)

    loop For each SyncEvent
        Poller->>Val: validate_event(event)

        alt INSERT operation
            Val->>Val: validate_source_table(catalog.schema.table)
            Val-->>SOp: Validated

            SOp->>DData: Read source data (Statement Execution API)
            DData-->>SOp: Polars DataFrame

            SOp->>SQL: Bulk INSERT into target_table
            SQL-->>SOp: rows_affected

        else UPDATE operation
            Val->>Val: validate_primary_keys(PKs required)
            Val->>Val: validate_source_table()
            Val-->>SOp: Validated

            SOp->>DData: Read source data with filter
            DData-->>SOp: Polars DataFrame

            SOp->>SQL: UPDATE ... SET ... WHERE pk = ?
            SQL-->>SOp: rows_affected

        else DELETE operation
            Val->>Val: validate_primary_keys(PKs required)
            Val->>Val: validate_delete_limit(max 10,000 rows)
            Val-->>SOp: Validated

            SOp->>SQL: DELETE FROM target WHERE pk IN (...)
            SQL-->>SOp: rows_affected
        end

        alt Success
            SOp->>ETbl: UPDATE status = 'completed'
            SOp->>WS: broadcast(event: completed)
        else Failure
            SOp->>ETbl: UPDATE status = 'failed', error = msg

            alt can_retry (< max_retries)
                Note over SOp: Exponential backoff
                SOp->>ETbl: UPDATE status = 'pending' (retry)
            else max_retries exceeded
                SOp->>WS: broadcast(event: failed)
            end
        end
    end
